    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240\u00b0C /220\u00b0C (fan) / gas 9 and boil a kettle</p><p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-pork-chilli-with-herby-rice-and-popped-beans/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced red onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 10 min or until slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-pork-chilli-with-herby-rice-and-popped-beans/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the onion softens, drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong>, reserving the liquid</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>black beans</strong> to a baking tray (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Drizzle them with<strong> olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the skins have burst and are crispy \u2013 these are your<strong> popped</strong> <strong>beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-pork-chilli-with-herby-rice-and-popped-beans/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the black beans are in the oven, dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[455ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> ground cinnamon</strong> to the red onion and cook for 1 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-pork-chilli-with-herby-rice-and-popped-beans/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Increase the heat to high, add the your <strong>mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to the pan and cook for 5-6 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-pork-chilli-with-herby-rice-and-popped-beans/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan</p><p>Cook for 1 min, then add the <strong>beef</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and a large pinch of<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 10 min or until slightly thickened in consistency</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>black beans</strong> with the <strong>reserved black bean liquid</strong> and cook for a further 5 min or until the sauce has thickened to a chilli-like consistency and the meat is cooked through (no pink meat!)\u2013 this is your <strong>smoky chilli</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-pork-chilli-with-herby-rice-and-popped-beans/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chilli is cooking, trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Once the rice is cooked, mix through the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>herby rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-lean-pork-chilli-with-herby-rice-and-popped-beans/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoky chilli</strong> over the <strong>herby rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>popped beans</strong> and <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
